author: Jason Silverstein
title: Georgia gov. didn't know asymptomatic people can spread virus
description: The CDC is headquartered in Georgia and has warned repeatedly about the risk of asymptomatic spread.
content: The governor of Georgia — the state where the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention is headquartered — said Wednesday he had only just learned that the coronavirus can be spread by people who aren't showing any symptoms. Public health officials have been… [+2079 chars]
